!! Question

The tools must be able to run inside the Claude.ai sandbox, there is no chance to install a browser and login to web page.

!! Answer ⟨kimik26instant · 0s⟩

Since you cannot run a browser or authenticate in the sandbox, you need a **pure Python static pipeline** that works on raw HTML or API-provided content. No single library handles all of this, but a combination of `BeautifulSoup`, `markdownify`, and `pylatexenc` runs entirely in the sandbox and preserves math, links, and sources.

## Recommended Sandbox-Safe Stack

| Component | Purpose | Sandbox Safe |
|---|---|---|
| `beautifulsoup4` | Parse HTML and statically extract LaTeX from MathJax/KaTeX tags | Yes |
| `markdownify` | Convert cleaned HTML to Markdown while preserving links | Yes {{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT017||CIT}}{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT018||CIT}} |
| `pylatexenc` | Sanitize Google Unicode math symbols into LaTeX | Yes {{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT019||CIT}}{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT020||CIT}} |
| `requests` | Fetch raw HTML if the page is publicly accessible | Yes |

## The Pipeline

### 1. Extract Math Before Markdown Conversion
Rendered math must be pulled out of the HTML **before** conversion, because markdownify will otherwise strip or garble the DOM nodes.

**MathJax (v2 and v3)** embeds the raw TeX in `<script type="math/tex">` tags or inside `<annotation encoding="application/x-tex">` within MathML.{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT021||CIT}}{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT022||CIT}}
**KaTeX** often stores the original LaTeX in a `data-latex` attribute or inside `<span class="katex-mathml">`.{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT023||CIT}}

Use BeautifulSoup to find these nodes, replace them with numbered placeholders (`__MATH_0__`), and store the LaTeX in a list.

### 2. Convert Remaining HTML to Markdown
Pass the cleaned HTML through `markdownify`. It preserves anchor links and basic structure while avoiding JavaScript dependencies.{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT024||CIT}}

### 3. Re-insert LaTeX
Replace the placeholders with the stored LaTeX wrapped in `$...$` or `{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_EQ0001||EQ}}` blocks.

### 4. Sanitize Unicode Math
Run the final Markdown text through `pylatexenc.latexencode.unicode_to_latex()`. This catches Google-style Unicode mathematical characters (e.g., `𝑥`, `𝐴`, `∫`) that were rendered as raw Unicode instead of LaTeX, converting them into proper escape sequences.{{Pplx20260623_DueYouKnow_CIT025||CIT}}

